 $\\\arcsin x+\arcsin (1-x)=\arccos x\\\implies\sin(\arcsin x+\arcsin(1-x))=\sin\arccos x\\\implies\sin(\arcsin x)\cos(\arcsin(1-x))+\cos(\arcsin x)\sin(\arcsin(1-x))=\cos(x)\\\implies(x)(\sqrt{1-(1-x)^2})+(\sqrt{1-x^2})(1-x)=\cos(x)\\\\\implies x\sqrt{2x-x^2}+(1-x)\sqrt{1-x^2}=\cos(x)\\\\\implies\sqrt{2x-x^3}+x^3+2x^2+x+x\sqrt{1-x^2}-2x-x^3=\cos(x)\\\\\implies\sqrt{2x-x^3}+x^3+2x^2+x+x\sqrt{1-x^2}-2x-x^3=\cos(x)\\\\\implies\sqrt{\dfrac{1}{x^2}-x}+\dfrac{1}{x^2}-1+2+\dfrac{1}{x}+1-\sqrt{\dfrac{1}{x}-1}-1=0\\\implies\dfrac{1}{x^2}-\sqrt{\dfrac{1}{x^4}-\dfrac{2}{x^3}+\dfrac{1}{x^2}}+\dfrac{1}{x}+\dfrac{2}{x}-\sqrt{\dfrac{1}{x^2}-1}=0\\\\\implies\dfrac{1}{x^2}-\left(\dfrac{1}{x}-\sqrt{\dfrac{2}{x^3}+\dfrac{1}{x^4}}\right)+\dfrac{1}{x}+\dfrac{2}{x}-\left(\dfrac{1}{x}-\sqrt{1-\dfrac{1}{x^2}}\right)=0\\\implies\dfrac{1}{x^2}+\dfrac{1}{x}-\sqrt{\dfrac{2}{x^3}+\dfrac{1}{x^2}}+\dfrac{2}{x}+\sqrt{1-\dfrac{1}{x^2}}=0\approx\dfrac{1}{x^2}+\dfrac{3}{x}-\sqrt{\dfrac{2}{x^3}+\dfrac{1}{x^2}}+\sqrt{1-\dfrac{1}{x^2}}=0 \ \because\sqrt{\dfrac{2}{x^3}+\dfrac{1}{x^4}}\approx0\\\therefore\dfrac{1}{x^2}+\dfrac{3}{x}-\sqrt{\dfrac{2}{x^3}+\dfrac{1}{x^2}}+\sqrt{1-\dfrac{1}{x^2}}=0\ \because\sqrt{\dfrac{2}{x^3}+\dfrac{1}{x^4}}\approx0\end{tham}> The equation under doubt is 
