\\ P21P31 = \sqrt{(0-2)^2+(1-2)^2}= \sqrt{5} \\ P22P32 = \sqrt{(1+2)^2+(2-1)^2}= \sqrt{10}\\ P23P33 = \sqrt{(0-(-2))^2+(1-2)^2}= \sqrt{5} \\ P31P32 = \sqrt{(1-(-2))^2+(2-1)^2}=3 \implies a \sqrt{b}=3 \sqrt{1} \\ \implies a+b =4
{/eq}
The number of units in the length of the longest side is $3\sqrt{1}$, so $a+b = \boxed{4}$.

